message: What is the difference between SarawakID and SarawakID Corp?
response: The difference between SarawakID and SarawakID Corp lies in their functions and purposes: SarawakID: This is a digital identity system designed for residents of Sarawak to access various government services online. It serves as a single sign-on platform, allowing users to manage their personal information and access services conveniently. SarawakID Corp: This refers to the corporate entity responsible for managing and overseeing the SarawakID system. It handles the development, maintenance, and enhancement of the digital identity platform, ensuring it meets user needs and complies with relevant regulations. If you have any additional questions or need further clarification, feel free to ask!

message: I cant register my SarawakID bc it says that my IC has been registered before, what should i do
response: If your SarawakID registration is indicating that your IC has been registered before, it may mean that there is an existing account associated with your IC number. Hereâ€™s what you can do: Contact Support: Reach out to the SarawakID support team for assistance. They can help resolve issues related to duplicate registrations or provide guidance on how to proceed. Visit a Service Sarawak Kiosk or Counter: You can go in person to a Service Sarawak Kiosk or Counter with your MyKad to verify your identity and get assistance with the registration issue. Check for Existing Account: If you have previously registered, try to recover your existing account by using the password recovery options or contacting support for help with accessing your account. These steps should help you resolve the issue with the registration of your SarawakID.
